When a Chinese characters are used in the Display name for an user. The display name gets truncated and limited to four characters in the review coverage report at the Individual Committer Stats section. Out of the four characters displayed, the last character failed to render properly as shown in the example below:-

E.G
The display name of the user is

{noformat}
姓姓姓姓姓 姓姓姓姓姓
{noformat}

However, it gets displayed as 
{noformat}
姓姓姓&
{noformat}

https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/FISHKB/Indexed+paths+truncated+at+10000

{quote}
By default FishEye/Crucible processes a maximum of 10000 change paths per changeset. This is to prevent extremely large changesets (which are often the result of human error) from slowing FishEye/Crucible down.
{quote}

This property is only used as a limit for indexing paths. All other commit processing (indexing diffs, LoC,..) is still done, so it is still not possible for FishEye to commits with large number of paths.

If we have case-insensitive Perforce repository with a file tree like:
{noformat}
FOO/Zebra
Foo/Apple
{noformat}

Fisheye (incorrectly) sorts the paths case sensitively, as above but then (correctly) combines directories which are case insensitively identical, ending up with a tree:

{noformat}
FOO - Zebra
    - Apple
{noformat}

It would be nice to have following type of special operators in FishEye quick search. For example, to search content with both 'database' and 'user' terms:

Quick Serach: "Content: database && user" 
Corresponding EyeQL search:
{code}
select revisions from dir "/" where content matches "database" and content matches "user" order by date  desc  group by changeset return path, revision, author, date, csid
{code}

Currently, code context is showing mangled in search results:

{code}
package com.squareup.swipe import com.squareup.wavpool.swipe.recorder import com.squareup.wavpool.swipe.wavpoolmodule import dagger.module import dagger.provides import javax.inject.singleton...provides @singleton recorder provideloggingrecorder registerrecorder recorder return recorder
{code}

Both newlines and case are critical for processing this context. I would expect to be able to read this as I read code.

